      "message": "Building Flutter appears to be very dependent on this structure, I tried many different ways of trying to change the directory name but ran into errors because this structure is hardcoded in their tools. \u0027src/flutter\u0027 is documented in their docs: https://github.com/brianosman/engine/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md and in the doc Kevin wrote: https://docs.google.com/document/d/19VuU-NPRvnj7eavH9Pwb8wfljpKBe-XWkVzuvnfDRtE/edit#heading\u003dh.hpzbjgghz5rt\n\nThe problem is that Chromium also uses src in our recipes. Chromium is only built for CommandBuffer (Mac) builds and RecreateSKPs (GCE). I tested on a bot by building Flutter first and then building RecreateSKPs and it seemed to work.\nOne way to make sure nothing unexpected happens would be to throw an exception if both need_flutter_checkout and need_chromium_checkout are true.",
